The Authority which the Apoſtle brings for this Doctrine, ſc. the Word of God; This I ſay unto you by the word of the Lord. He quotes divine Authority for what he delivereth. It being a Doctrine of ſo much encouragement and ſatisfaction unto dying Saints;
Praefatur, nihil ſe preferre vel ſuum, vel humanum, Calv. a Doctrine above humane capacity, and (it ſeemeth) not commonly underſtood by the Churches & Saints of God at that time; he doth not paſs it in his own name, or upon his own Authority, When he ſpeaks as one that hath obtained mercy to be ſaithful, then it is 1 Cor. 7.12. I ſpeak, not the Lord, i.e. not by expreſs dictate of the Spirit, but by way of Faith, Chriſtivice, as agreeable to the word: but when he ſpeaks as an Apoſtle, inſallibly inſpired, then it is, not I, but the Lord: and ſo it is here. but tells us from whence he had it, q.d. What I deliver now unto you, I
ſpeak not of my ſelf, ſed ex ore Domini, from the mouth of him that is the truth it ſelf, the mouth of Jeſus Chriſt; This we ſay unto you in the word of the Lord.

